.TH "dsa_tree_notify" 9 "dsa_tree_notify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dsa_tree_notify \- Execute code for all switches in a DSA switch tree.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dsa_tree_notify
.BI "(struct dsa_switch_tree *dst "  ","
.BI "unsigned long e "  ","
.BI "void *v "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
collection of struct dsa_switch devices to notify.
.IP "e" 12
event, must be of type DSA_NOTIFIER_*
.IP "v" 12
event-specific value.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given a struct dsa_switch_tree, this can be used to run a function once for
each member DSA switch. The other alternative of traversing the tree is only
through its ports list, which does not uniquely list the switches.
